---
/**
 * Accessibility statement — WCAG 2.2 AA target, real commitments, contact
 * path. Per design doc §11.5 and §14 (state-plus-text badges, reduced
 * motion, skip-to-main). This is not a boilerplate page; it names the
 * specific techniques we use and asks to be tested against them.
 */
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '2026-04-18';
---
<Layout
  title="Accessibility — privacy.whattheflip.lol"
  description="WCAG 2.2 AA target. Keyboard navigable, screen-reader friendly, honors prefers-reduced-motion. State badges use text plus color. Report issues to the pseudonymous contact."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl py-6 space-y-6 prose-zinc prose-invert">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="text-sm text-text-muted">
      <a href="/en/" class="hover:text-text">Home</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true" class="px-2">/</span>
      <span class="text-text">Accessibility</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="space-y-2">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-text sm:text-4xl">Accessibility</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Last updated <time datetime={lastUpdated}>{lastUpdated}</time>.</p>
    </header>

    <section class="space-y-3 text-text leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Target</h2>
      <p>
        This site targets <strong>WCAG 2.2 Level AA</strong>. Where we fall short, we want to know.
        Accessibility is a privacy issue: a site you cannot read does not protect you.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3 text-text leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">What we promise</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
        <li>
          <strong>Keyboard navigation.</strong> Every control is reachable with <kbd>Tab</kbd>. Skip
          link at the top of each page jumps past the navigation into <code>#main</code>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Screen readers.</strong> Hero demos, scanner state, and interactive controls carry
          <code>aria-live</code>, <code>aria-label</code>, and <code>role</code> attributes. Tested
          with NVDA, VoiceOver, and Orca.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Reduced motion.</strong> The Ghost Demo and any animated state changes honor
          <code>prefers-reduced-motion: reduce</code>. If set, animations become instant transitions
          and no looping motion runs.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Text-plus-color badges.</strong> The scanner's five Defense Mode states
          (Private / Leaking / Farbled / Spoofed / Unchanged) all carry readable text labels in
          addition to color. Color is never the only cue. See the{' '}
          <a href="/en/scan" class="underline">scanner</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Contrast.</strong> All body text is 4.5:1 or better against its background. Large
          text and non-text UI elements are 3:1 or better.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>No autoplay.</strong> No video or audio starts without explicit click. No
          pop-ups, no modals that grab focus on load.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3 text-text leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Known issues</h2>
      <p>
        The scanner uses a technical visualization ("Ghost Demo") that may be confusing on first
        glance. Every Ghost element carries a text label and a
        <code>title</code> attribute — if those are not enough, please report it and we will add
        plain-text descriptions in the caption area.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3 text-text leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Report an issue</h2>
      <p>
        If any part of this site does not work for you with your assistive technology, or any piece
        of content is unreadable, we want the specific page and the specific problem. Email:
        <a href="mailto:claude.aiactuallall.disregard729@passmail.com" class="underline">claude.aiactuallall.disregard729@passmail.com</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Reports are acknowledged within 3 business days and fixes are prioritized. The fix lands in
        a dated entry in <a href="/en/changelog" class="underline">the changelog</a> — this is how
        we keep ourselves honest.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3 text-text leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Testing cadence</h2>
      <p>
        Automated (axe-core, Lighthouse) runs on every build. Manual keyboard and screen-reader
        passes run at release boundaries. An independent third-party audit is committed for the
        12-month mark. That commitment is also in <a href="/en/about" class="underline">the founder note</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
